Global Active Steering Market Insights
Active Steering Market size was valued at USD 3.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 5.7 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.2% from 2024 to 2030.

Active Steering Market Overview
The active steering market has witnessed substantial growth, with a market size valued at approximately USD 7.5 billion in 2024, expected to reach USD 13.4 billion by 2032, growing at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 7.5%. The market's expansion is driven by the increasing demand for enhanced driving experience, safety features, and fuel efficiency. Active steering technology is becoming a key feature in modern vehicles, enhancing maneuverability, stability, and overall vehicle handling. As a result, several automakers are investing heavily in active steering systems, making them a critical component of automotive development. With continuous innovation in electric vehicles (EVs) and autonomous driving, active steering is poised for significant advancements and applications in the coming years.

